comments.body:
#1192 is somewhat related where we played around with the idea of a common executable or script.

C:\program files\powershell\powershell.exe as a symbolic link to a version-specific instance of PowerShell Core would satisfy the requirement.

@iSazonov - We constructed the module paths so that the default paths do not overlap. Path resolution conflicts for executables are handled in a first-come-first-served, so users will have to include the path to PowerShell Core's exe before that of Windows PowerShell if they want it to be their default powershell.
